<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12038j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12038j">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12038j"> 38(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 99 huguenots buried / killed 29&frasl;ix&frasl;591</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> suivant l&apos;expression si vraie et si pittoresque du trouv&egrave;re Benoit de Saint-More. Il fallait enjamber les d&eacute;bris de cet escalier qui s&apos;&eacute;levait de la fontaine Saint-Aubert, au tourillon conique, jusqu&apos;&agrave; la porte basse des Montgommeries; on &eacute;tait oblig&eacute; d&apos;&eacute;carter d&apos;&eacute;paisses broussailles &agrave; l&apos;endroit m&ecirc;me o&ugrave; furent enterr&eacute;s les <mark>&lsquo;nonante-huict&rsquo; huguenots, tu&eacute;s dans la nuit du 28 au 29 septembre 1591</mark>. <br><font color="green">[&hellip; according to the true and picturesque expression of the troubadour Benoit de Saint-More. You had to climb over the ruins of the stairs that used to go from the fountain of Saint-Aubert, with the conic trunnion, all the way to the low gate of the Montgommeries; you were obliged to push aside the thick brush at the same spot <mark>where the 98 Huguenots were buried, killed on the night of 28 and 29 September 1591</mark>.]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="SMIN" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SMIN"><cite title="source">Le Mont Saint-Michel Inconnu</cite></a> (1912) 13</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
